Configuration notes:
http://www.jasondavies.com/wordcloud/about/


Make sure not to fall for this issue:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17551985/collision-with-word-cloud-generator-d3-js


---
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17526020/d3-word-clouds-too-much-overlaps-occurring

Found the solution. I was not using the rotate() function call as i want text to be horizontally placed. i thought leaving out the call entirely would help.
appears not to be the case. so i add rotate (0) and that's it. now i get a good-looking word cloud.
TIP: i use stroke: black against text styles and this gives a neat presentation.

---
Some more discussions on using it:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14448482/d3-library-how-to-access-data-from-json-in-this-example